Package com.cafean.document.notebook.util

Class IndexedValueMap

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.cafean.document.notebook.util.IndexedValueMap
  • public class IndexedValueMap
extends java.lang.Object
    A class used to organize a set of indexed values (such as junction flags) that are stored by location but should be output by value.

    For example:

    Edge Geometry Data
    PropertyLocationsValue
    Area1, 5-7 0.0
    2-4 1.0

      • add

        public void add​(java.lang.Object value,
                int location)
        adds the given value/location pair to this map. Note that if the given value already exists in the map the size of the map will remain the same.
        Parameters:
        value - the value at the given location
        location - the location of the given value

      • indexOf

        public int indexOf​(java.lang.Object value)
        Returns the index in this map of the given value. Note that this index is not the location that the value is used but rather the index into this map as used by getValue.

        public java.lang.Object getDescription​(java.lang.Object value)
